{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Summary\n`rebar bridge-fsck` reports \"no issues found\" while three real drift classes exist (a dangling confirmed binding, archived-local-with-live-Jira bindings, and an unbound Jira-native issue). Its checks are structurally blind to all of them.\n\n## Root Cause (offline local-event scan; never reads bindings.json or Jira)\n- `audit_bridge_mappings` (`bridge_fsck.py:59-183`) walks per-ticket event-log dirs under `.tickets-tracker/` only (`:102-127`); it has ZERO references to `bindings.json`, Jira, or acli.\n- Its three checks: Orphan = SYNC-without-CREATE (`:137-139`); Duplicate = same `jira_key` on >=2 ticket dirs (`:141-143`,`:173-176`); Stale SYNC = latest SYNC >30d with no later BRIDGE_ALERT (`:145-171`). None can see: a confirmed binding whose Jira issue was deleted; a binding whose local ticket is archived while Jira stays live; or a Jira-native issue with no binding.\n- The detector that WOULD catch these (`reconcile_check.py:229-259`, `orphaned_bindings` / `orphaned_jira`) is report-only and NOT on the `bridge-fsck` path; it also needs a live Jira fetch, so it cannot run offline.\n\n## Detector landscape (from a full inventory)\n- Two disjoint families: OFFLINE (`bridge-fsck`, local events only) and ONLINE (invariants `check_dual_identity_complete` `invariants.py:228`; differ `dd-5` dangling-jira-ref `differ.py:240,426`; `reconcile_check`). The healing-capable ones run ONLY inside a live reconcile pass; `reconcile_check` is the only binding-aware read-only detector but is report-only and needs Jira.\n- No detector reads `bindings.json` in an offline path.\n- Dead code: `bridge_fsck.enumerate_*` parallel enumerators (per `docs/maintenance-audit-runbook.md:121`).\n\n## History (why the families are separate / unwired)\n- Both `audit_bridge_mappings` and `reconcile_check` were introduced in the SAME commit `b534f47a7` (\"Extract DSO ticket system + Jira reconciler into standalone rebar\") — inherited VERBATIM from DSO, never engineered as a rebar decision.\n- `e15907dd0` (\"bridge-fsck audit in-process\") ported `audit_bridge_mappings` as the \"canonical\" fast offline scan and deliberately left the one Jira-touching enumerator dead. `reconcile_check` never got an offline arm (docstring frames it as the live-fetch diagnostic; `docs/jira-sync-setup.md:144,389`).\n- No commit/ADR/doc ever proposed unifying the families or giving `bridge-fsck` a bindings.json-aware mode.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. With a dangling confirmed binding present (e.g. f8b5 -> deleted REB-530), run `rebar bridge-fsck`.\n2. Observe \"No issues found\" despite the drift.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: `bridge-fsck` (or a companion audit) flags dangling bindings, archived-local-with-live-Jira bindings, and unbound Jira-native issues.\n- Actual: it reports clean; the drift is invisible.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] An offline audit reads `bindings.json` and flags: (a) a confirmed binding whose Jira side is gone, (b) a binding whose local ticket is archived/deleted while Jira stays live, (c) [with a Jira snapshot] an unbound Jira-native issue.\n- [ ] Either `bridge-fsck` gains a bindings.json-aware check, or `reconcile_check`'s binding-aware detectors are wired to a reachable audit surface (CLI/lib/MCP), with the offline/online split documented.\n- [ ] The dead `bridge_fsck.enumerate_*` code is removed or wired.\n- [ ] A RED test: a fixture with a dangling confirmed binding -> the audit flags it (currently returns clean).\n\n## Notes\nDiscovered comparing Jira REB vs local. Files: `bridge_fsck.py`, `reconcile_check.py`, `__main__.py`, `invariants.py`, `differ.py`; docs `jira-sync-setup.md`, `maintenance-audit-runbook.md`.\n\n## Guardrails (must-preserve — prior-art + archaeology; folds in the corrected plan)\n- [ ] ONE pure classifier `classify(local, jira, binding, baseline) -> Decision`, TWO consumers: the live pass ACTS on it; the audit REPORTS it. Detection becomes the enforcement mechanism (no more report-only/healing fork).\n- [ ] `bridge-fsck` reads `bindings.json` READ-ONLY and never becomes a write path that bypasses the rebar-id label-write audit (L9).\n- [ ] Offline mode runs the matrix cells decidable without Jira (archived-local, dangling-local); online mode (with a Jira snapshot) runs the full matrix — folding in `reconcile_check`'s `orphaned_bindings`/`orphaned_jira` detectors (`reconcile_check.py:229-259`).\n- [ ] Report mode is the PARITY ORACLE: it surfaces the true drift set that every heal is validated against; wire it to alert (open a ticket) on unhealed drift.\n- [ ] Remove the dead `bridge_fsck.enumerate_*` parallel enumerators."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783078760298238001,"uuid":"b4bf797f-9940-4aec-818e-090367d322ee"}